Sentencas: LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-delta and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-delta compositions were selected as air-side contact materials candidates for reversible solid oxide fuel cells (RSOFCs) electrodes based on their structural features and electrical properties.
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: These perovskites were synthesized through a combustion method.
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Neutron powder diffraction was performed to examine structural modifications of the phases over a wide range of temperatures (from room temperature to 900 degrees C).
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Both materials exhibit a rhombohedra (R-3c) structure in the measured temperature range.
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: A noticeable oxygen deficiency is observed at the application temperature in RSOFCs (i.e., 800 degrees C), with a refined stoichiometry of oxygen of 2.71(1) and 2.90(1) per formula unit in LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-delta and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cu0.2O3-delta at 900 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: An electrical conductivity (sigma) of 234 S cm(-1) was measured for LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-delta at 800 degrees C, while a slightly higher sigma value was achieved for LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-delta perovskite (277 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C).
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: An average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of approximate to 13 x 10(-6) K-1 (25-900 degrees C, air) was measured for both compositions.
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Furthermore, we confirm compatibility of the synthesized materials with RSOFC stack components: the electrodes (La0.3Ca0.7Fe0.7Cr0.3O3-delta) and interconnects (Crofer 22 APU).
Titulo: Crystal structure and electrical properties of LaNi0.6Fe0.2Cu0.2O3-δ and LaNi0.6Fe0.3Cr0.1O3-δ perovskites: Contact materials for reversible solid oxide fuel cell electrodes
